{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This'll damage the whole campaign.

1292
01:25:12,065 --> 01:25:14,484
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look, you do it your way, and we'll do it ours, all right?

1293
01:25:14,693 --> 01:25:16,110
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can read our demands.

1294
01:25:16,361 --> 01:25:18,362
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Go back to your cells.

1295
01:25:18,739 --> 01:25:20,031
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blankets!

1296
01:25:20,699 --> 01:25:22,617
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For God's sake, put a stop to this.

1297
01:25:22,701 --> 01:25:24,535
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're weakening my position, Guiseppe.

1298
01:25:24,620 --> 01:25:26,496
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It will end in violence. Good.

1299
01:25:26,580 --> 01:25:27,747
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's good about it?

1300
01:25:27,831 --> 01:25:28,915
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's all they understand.

1301
01:25:32,002 --> 01:25:33,961
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Barker refused to negotiate.

1302
01:25:34,046 --> 01:25:36,255
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But with the screws gone, we'd a brief taste of freedom.

1303
01:25:36,340 --> 01:25:37,548
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Check out Ronnie!

1304
01:25:39,718 --> 01:25:41,052
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Him swallow half Africa.

1305
01:25:42,888 --> 01:25:44,263
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I give him about an hour.

1306
01:25:51,254 --> 01:25:53,523
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We found out later our protest got on TV.

1307
01:25:54,191 --> 01:25:56,067
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And that's when the riot squad was ordered in.

1308
01:26:12,042 --> 01:26:13,918
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We were singled out as the ringleaders.

1309
01:26:14,253 --> 01:26:15,294
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now!

1310
01:26:40,863 --> 01:26:42,947
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You just signed your own death warrant, Barker.

1311
01:26:47,786 --> 01:26:48,911
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you happy now?

1312
01:26:53,125 --> 01:26:55,334
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And then you arrived, Gareth.

1313
01:26:55,586 --> 01:26:59,714
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's the first time I saw you, under a raining shower of sparks.

1314
01:26:59,798 --> 01:27:03,676
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It was the first time I'd seen a woman in five years, other than my mother.

1315
01:27:03,760 --> 01:27:06,012
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But to me, you were a lawyer first.

1316
01:27:06,096 --> 01:27:07,305
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I hated lawyers.

1317
01:27:07,389 --> 01:27:08,723
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And do you have a new isolation room?

1318
01:27:10,893 --> 01:27:12,727
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bert, Andrew.

1319
01:27:12,978 --> 01:27:16,147
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bailey, Benjamin. McAndrew, Joseph.

1320
01:27:16,231 --> 01:27:18,649
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sorry. Can you... I can't hear. Conlon, Gerard.

1321
01:27:19,026 --> 01:27:20,693
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}O'Brien, John.

1322
01:27:21,320 --> 01:27:24,739
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lynch, Bernard. Crisp, Quincy.

1323
01:27:25,032 --> 01:27:27,950
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lyon, Richard. Burns, Delrow.

1324
01:27:28,160 --> 01:27:29,702
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What about Conlon?

1325
01:27:29,786 --> 01:27:31,871
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sorry. Guiseppe Conlon.

1326
01:27:32,497 --> 01:27:34,123
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's on the third floor.

1327
01:27:35,083 --> 01:27:37,835
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He has difficulty getting down the stairs.

1328
01:27:39,338 --> 01:27:41,881
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, I'll just have to go up and see him then.

1329
01:27:41,965 --> 01:27:44,508
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The delegation has seen enough. Right-o. Sorry.

1330
01:27:44,843 --> 01:27:47,845
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, I won't be a minute. I'll just... Is that all right? Sorry.

1331
01:27:48,889 --> 01:27:51,307
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll meet you outside, okay? Sorry.

1332
01:27:58,106 --> 01:27:59,273
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sorry, I can't...

1333
01:27:59,358 --> 01:28:00,524
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pulmonary thrombosis.

1334
01:28:00,609 --> 01:28:01,943
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you're getting medication...

1335
01:28:02,027 --> 01:28:03,110
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's getting proper medication?

1336
01:28:03,195 --> 01:28:04,278
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you? Yes?

1337
01:28:09,701 --> 01:28:10,701
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Son?

1338
01:28:11,203 --> 01:28:12,370
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gerry!

1339
01:28:13,538 --> 01:28:15,414
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's... Is it Gerry?

1340
01:28:15,499 --> 01:28:16,749
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's Gerry. Uh-huh.

1341
01:28:16,833 --> 01:28:19,168
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's had a spot of bother with lawyers in the past.

1342
01:28:23,215 --> 01:28:25,716
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's all yours. Fifteen minutes.

1343
01:28:26,468 --> 01:28:27,843
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you. Sit down.

1344
01:28:35,435 --> 01:28:36,811
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You wanted to see me, Gerry?

1345
01:28:57,874 --> 01:29:00,167
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why are you giving my father false hope?

1346
01:29:01,003 --> 01:29:02,169
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sorry?

1347
01:29:03,005 --> 01:29:05,256
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's been up and down these stairs every couple of weeks to see you.

1348
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:07,133
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He hasn't even seen my mother in six months.

1349
01:29:07,217 --> 01:29:10,386
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, I hear you're getting on very well with her, by the way.

1350
01:29:10,470 --> 01:29:12,596
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes. She's a very brave woman.

1351
01:29:13,181 --> 01:29:14,515
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Aye, you don't know the half of it.

1352
01:29:17,728 --> 01:29:19,103
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The fucking stairs are killing him.

1353
01:29:19,855 --> 01:29:21,939
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's not the stairs that are killing your father, Gerry.

1354
01:29:22,441 --> 01:29:23,774
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why, what is it, then?

1355
01:29:23,859 --> 01:29:25,151
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's your lack of faith.

1356
01:29:25,944 --> 01:29:28,195
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lack of faith? Faith in what?

1357
01:29:28,822 --> 01:29:29,989
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}In yourself.

1358
01:29:30,282 --> 01:29:32,825
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, I have faith in myself.

1359
01:29:34,286 --> 01:29:37,955
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gerry Conlon, lifer, 30-year sentence.

1360
01:29:38,415 --> 01:29:39,999
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I know how to survive it. No problem.

1361
01:29:41,793 --> 01:29:42,960
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}At what price?

1362
01:29:43,295 --> 01:29:45,379
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll pay the fucking price. Don't you worry about it.

1363
01:29:46,298 --> 01:29:48,049
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The price for what?

1364
01:29:50,302 --> 01:29:52,845
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're very good at the English, aren't you?

1365
01:29:53,722 --> 01:29:56,515
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You see, I don't understand your language.

1366
01:29:58,435 --> 01:30:01,520
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Justice. Mercy. Clemency.

1367
01:30:02,147 --> 01:30:05,399
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I literally don't understand what those words mean.

1368
01:30:05,901 --> 01:30:08,903
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You see, I'd like to put in an application to get all my teeth extracted.

1369
01:30:08,987 --> 01:30:10,738
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And that way I could put my fist in my mouth

1370
01:30:10,822 --> 01:30:13,449
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and never speak another word of fuckin' English so long as I live...

1371
01:30:13,533 --> 01:30:15,659
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you see what I'm saying, Miss Peirce? Mrs. Peirce, is it?

1372
01:30:16,703 --> 01:30:18,204
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you trying to impress me?

1373
01:30:20,373 --> 01:30:21,665
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Visit's up.

1374
01:30:22,334 --> 01:30:25,169
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't give my father false hope, all right?

1375
01:30:25,462 --> 01:30:27,171
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gerry!

1376
01:30:28,507 --> 01:30:30,174
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, you've got to help him!

1377
01:30:32,552 --> 01:30:35,596
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}In prison, you pray for anything to break the monotony.

1378
01:30:35,680 --> 01:30:38,349
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A snowstorm is like a present from God.

1379
01:30:47,776 --> 01:30:49,360
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stop!

1380
01:30:49,444 --> 01:30:50,778
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Prison officers are not to be hit!

1381
01:30:51,696 --> 01:30:53,364
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right, you lot, you've asked for it.

1382
01:30:56,034 --> 01:30:58,911
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After the riot, my father's health deteriorated badly.

1383
01:30:59,496 --> 01:31:02,456
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He couldn't make it down the stairs to enjoy the snow.

1384
01:31:02,541 --> 01:31:05,918
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I waved up to him, but he was looking at something else.

1385
01:31:16,179 --> 01:31:18,180
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My da always saw the good in people.

1386
01:31:18,890 --> 01:31:22,059
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He recognized it in you the minute he saw you, Gareth.

1387
01:31:22,477 --> 01:31:23,811
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Guv, guv, where you going?

1388
01:31:23,895 --> 01:31:26,230
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where's me letters? Guv'nor!

1389
01:31:30,360 --> 01:31:31,694
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you.

1390
01:31:36,158 --> 01:31:39,034
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I see you've been mentioned in Congress, Guiseppe.

1391
01:31:39,119 --> 01:31:40,536
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's that?

1392
01:31:47,419 --> 01:31:48,627
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How'd you come by that name?

1393
01:31:49,087 --> 01:31:52,173
